# Example environment configuration for the workshop project.
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the required secrets/values.
#
# Usage (Python):
#   pip install -r requirements.txt
#   export $(grep -v '^#' .env | xargs)  # or use `python-dotenv` if preferred
#
# Usage (Node examples):
#   (If you add variables for Node, load them with a library like `dotenv`.)
#
# --- API Keys & Model Config ---
# OpenAI model name to use for agents. Defaults in code to gpt-4o-mini if unset.
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# Optional: API key/token for the OpenAI-compatible provider if required by your runtime.
#OPENAI_API_KEY=replace_with_api_key

# (Deprecated) Previously used: OPENWEATHER_API_KEY for weather tool (now removed).
# You can safely ignore/remove that variable.

# --- Server Debug Flags ---
# Enable verbose/debug logging for the resources server (any non-empty value turns it on).
RESOURCES_SERVER_DEBUG=
# Enable verbose/debug logging for the prompts server.
PROMPTS_SERVER_DEBUG=
# Enable verbose/debug logging for the tools server.
TOOLS_SERVER_DEBUG=

# (Add additional variables below as new features require them.)
